review_blob:
Overall Im not a big fan of Terrapin brews, in fact I dont care for Terrapin Rye.  The Rye Squared is an entirely different animal.

In my opinion is has little resemblence with its "single" cousin.  This is a very good beer, and hoppier than I expected.  The color is fanstastic, great body despite not a lot carbonation.  

Im very surprised.

GABF 2007.  Im privileged to be one of the few who have had the opportunity to try this brew.  Exceptional in every way, I kept returning to have more.  Dark chocolate, wood, caramel... sample enough times and youll find a little bit of everything; a complex brew.
From 12oz bottle - dark with coffee and chocolate dominating.  I can barely taste the Perle and Centennial hops, but the malts are very evident.  Nice and sweet, this is a solid contender.

12oz bottle - 2007ish
Very dark, looks like motor oil, I cant see through the glass.  Fruity aromas, no head whatsover.  High alcohol but not as apparent as I thought.  Flavors are all over the place and lingering aftertaste stays with you.
This isnt my favorite double IPA but its good.  12 oz bottle had an overwhelming taste of grapefruit.  An earlier bottle from the same batch did not present that way.

This reminds me more of DFHs 120 minute IPA than the DEtre of which its based.  That said, there is a very apparent raisin flavor.  

This one sneaks up on you, enjoy with caution and over time.  Love the color and while the alcohol is apparent, it is not dominant.

Overall an excellent brew to savor.

12 oz bottle bottled Dec 2006- Full body, thick feel, beautiful copper color with soft carbonation - just right.   Obvious alcohol taste and aroma, but not overpowering.  Almost a liquorice flavor at times.  Savor this one, takes a long time to finish, good choice to share!
